# **AI Coding Agent Guide: Troubleshooting Tailwind CSS Not Applying**

Based on your screenshot and the search results, the issue is likely that Tailwind CSS classes aren't being applied properly. Here's a systematic troubleshooting approach:

## **Step 1: Force CSS Application with Important Classes**

Replace your booking bar code with this version that uses `!important` to override any conflicting styles:

```jsx
const BookingBar = ({
  checkInDate,
  setCheckInDate,
  checkOutDate,
  setCheckOutDate,
}: BookingBarProps) => {

  return (
    
      
        {/* Desktop Layout */}
        
          
          {/* Check-in Date */}
          
            
              
                
                  
                  {checkInDate ? format(checkInDate, "MMM dd") : Check-in}
                
              
              
                
              
            
          
          
          {/* Check-out Date */}
          
            
              
                
                  
                  {checkOutDate ? format(checkOutDate, "MMM dd") : Check-out}
                
              
              
                
              
            
          
          
          {/* Guests */}
          
            
              
                
                
              
              
                1 Guest
                2 Guests
                3 Guests
                4 Guests
                5+ Guests
              
            
          
          
          {/* Search Button */}
          
            
              Search
            
          
        
        
        {/* Mobile Layout - UNCHANGED */}
        
          {/* Keep existing mobile code exactly the same */}
        
      
    
  );
};
```

## **Step 2: Check Tailwind Configuration**

Verify your `tailwind.config.js` includes your component path:

```js
module.exports = {
  content: [
    "./src/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}",
    "./components/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}",  // Add this line
    "./app/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}",         // Add this if using app directory
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {},
  },
  plugins: [],
}
```

## **Step 3: Add Custom CSS Override**

Create a CSS file with aggressive overrides and import it in your component:

```css
/* booking-bar.css */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .booking-bar-compact .md\:compact-container {
    padding: 0.75rem !important;
    max-width: 420px !important;
    width: auto !important;
  }
  
  .booking-bar-compact .md\:compact-flex {
    display: flex !important;
    gap: 0.5rem !important;
  }
  
  .booking-bar-compact .md\:compact-field {
    width: 100px !important;
  }
  
  .booking-bar-compact .md\:compact-guests {
    width: 85px !important;
  }
  
  .booking-bar-compact .md\:compact-button-container {
    width: 90px !important;
  }
  
  .booking-bar-compact .md\:compact-element {
    height: 2rem !important;
    font-size: 0.75rem !important;
    padding-left: 0.5rem !important;
    padding-right: 0.5rem !important;
  }
  
  .booking-bar-compact .md\:compact-icon {
    height: 0.75rem !important;
    width: 0.75rem !important;
  }
}
```

Then update your component:

```jsx
import './booking-bar.css'; // Add this import

const BookingBar = ({ ... }) => {
  return (
    
      
        
          
          
            
              
                
                  
                  {checkInDate ? format(checkInDate, "MMM dd") : Check-in}
                
              
              {/* ... rest stays same ... */}
            
          
          
          {/* Repeat similar pattern for other fields */}
          
        
        {/* Mobile layout unchanged */}
      
    
  );
};
```
